-- Komercni, Erste Lead Biggest Gain for Czech Shares in Four Weeks
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-07T07:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/komercni-erste-lead-biggest-gain-for-czech-shares-in-four-weeks.html
Komercni Banka AS (KOMB) , Societe Generale
SA’s Czech unit, and  Austria ’s  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  led the
steepest gain for Czech shares in four weeks on speculation
policy makers around the world will stimulate economic growth.  Komercni Banka jumped 3.4 percent to 3,330 koruna, headed
for a fifth day of gains. Erste rose 2.2 percent to 374 koruna.
The 14-member  PX (PX)  index, in which the two lenders have a combined
35 percent weighting, added 1.5 percent, the most since May 10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  